cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS 

This paper proposes a novel quantization method for training and inference of neural networks, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper focuses on improving the accuracy and memory efficiency of deep neural networks. The paper also involves computer vision (cs.CV) as it evaluates the proposed method on image classification tasks using popular architectures such as ResNet and Inception. Additionally, the paper involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it proposes a new technique for quantization. The paper also involves neural networks (cs.NE) as it deals with the training and inference of deep neural networks. Finally, the paper involves data structures (cs.DS) as it proposes a new method for handling large and small data separately.
